analysis: The agent's function call semantically matched the task, but the reviewComments field used user-provided wording ("clear and well-recorded") instead of the expected phrasing ("transparent and well-documented"). The evaluator required an exact text match, leading to failure.
The agent used the year 2023 instead of 2024 for the requested date range, failing to align the function call with the user's travel timeframe and the expected scheduling parameters.

The agent's function call used paraphrased comments rather than exactly matching the expected wording, indicating a lack of strict adherence to the reference response. The core failure is the model's inability to preserve required comment phrasing for deterministic evaluation.

The agent called the analysis function with "feedbackId": "latest" instead of the expected "most-recent", failing to match the required function signature and thus was not recognized by the evaluator.

The agent only created the 'Supervisor' role inherited from 'Admin' but failed to include the previously defined 'Admin' and 'User' roles in the securityManagementAPI_setupUserRoles call, resulting in an incomplete role specification.

The agent provided a generic "communication skills" improvement area instead of specifying the feedback-identified subskills ("verbal communication" and "written communication"), missing the required detail for actionable training recommendations.

The agent's function call specified "priceRange": "150 euros" instead of the required "up to 150 euros per night," omitting the "per night" qualifier and the upper-limit intent, leading to a mismatch with the expected function call format.

The agent omitted "per night" from the budget parameter in the function call, providing just "$150" instead of the required "$150 per night", resulting in a parameter mismatch and failure to match the expected function call format.

The agent incorrectly structured the function call by omitting the required nesting: it placed travel_dates at the top level and did not nest all user preferences (including travel_dates) under user_preferences as specified in the function signature.
The agent submitted the review with "reviewReason" as "confirm compliance" instead of the expected "ensure compliance," failing to exactly match the required argument for the function call.

The agent omitted the required "notifications" parameter (with alert preferences) when calling festival_art_schedule_creator, resulting in an incomplete function call that did not conform to the expected function signature.

The agent incorrectly included the "frequency": "Weekly" field in the updatedToolSettings when only the "method": "Email" change was requested. The function call should have updated only the "method", not duplicated existing parameters.

The agent used the incorrect widget_id "inventory_status" instead of the expected "inventory_levels" for the inventory dashboard component, resulting in a function call that did not match the benchmark's required parameters.

The agent booked a restaurant named "Classic Italian Trattoria" with the location as "Rome" and added "Close to the Colosseum" as a special request, instead of booking "Traditional Italian Trattoria" with the correct location "near the Colosseum" as specified in the expected parameters.
The agent incorrectly used "influencer collaborations" instead of the required "influencer partnerships" as the Instagram strategy, resulting in a parameter mismatch with the expected function call.

The agent scheduled the meeting with the agenda "complete and sign the contract" instead of the expected "Finalize and sign the contract," causing a mismatch in the function call parameters and leading to evaluation failure.

The agent generated a report using an incorrect, averaged innovation rate (65% for both teams) instead of using the correct individual innovation rates (70% for Team Alpha and 60% for Team Beta) as provided in the input data.

The agent used "cuisine" as a tourist interest instead of mapping it to the expected "food" keyword, resulting in a parameter mismatch for the function call and failure to align with the accepted input schema.

The agent omitted the required insurance_cost parameter in the travel_budget_manager_calculate_travel_budget function call, even though the insurance cost ($120.5) was available from prior tool outputs and should have been included per the toolâ€™s specification.

The agent failed to include the required "pricingOptions" parameter with demand-driven algorithm and forecasting true in its function call, omitting key details necessary for the travelDealsAggregator_fetchDeals tool to apply demand forecasting and revenue management.

The agent's function call did not match the expected strict parameters; specifically, it used "comfortable cottage that includes breakfast" instead of the expected "cozy cottage with breakfast" for the preferences field, causing the evaluator to reject the call as non-matching.

The agent incorrectly included an extra parameter "feedback_type" in the manage_feedback_collection function call, which was not expected, resulting in a mismatch with the required function signature.

The agent failed to filter out the team led by the transactional leader before calling TrackInnovationMetrics_calculateInnovationRate, resulting in an incorrect function call that included irrelevant team data. Only transformational leader teams should have been included.

The agent altered the desired_qualities in the function arguments from "10 years of industry experience" and "excellent communication skills" to "at least 10 years of industry experience" and "outstanding communication abilities," causing a mismatch with the expected function call parameters.

The agent failed to properly close the JSON object in its tool call output, resulting in an incomplete and unparsable payload. This truncated the function arguments, causing a parsing error and preventing correct tool invocation.

The agent failed to normalize the user's interests to the expected schema by outputting "cultural experiences" and "unwinding" instead of the required "cultural tourism" and "relaxation," resulting in a function call mismatch despite otherwise correct structure and data.
